This memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama, delegates authority to the Secretary of State to determine whether it is important for the security interests of the United States to provide up to $28,970,312 of Fiscal Year 2015 Economic Support Fund resources for stabilization programs in Syria. This authority is given under section 614(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State is also directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.